HEADWORD: Patency
<hw>Pa"ten*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Patent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of being open,
enlarged, or spread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being patent or evident.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

